    {
      "para_id": "Q000873.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(1) For Ereškigal , lady of the place where the sun sets , Lu-Utu , governor of Umma , child of Ninisina , built a temple at the place where Utu rises , the place where the fates are determined for his ( own ) well-being . He laid out a canal at its edge . He made its name resplendent ."
    }
  ],
